            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In 2 presumably unrelated Turkish patients with microcephalic osteodysplastic primordial dwarfism type II (MOPD2; 210720), one from a consanguineous and the other from an apparently nonconsanguineous union, Rauch et al. (2008) identified homozygosity for a 1-bp insertion, 841_842insG, resulting in a frameshift at arg281 and a termination codon at position 327 (Arg281fsTer327). The patient from the nonconsanguineous union was born at 35 weeks' gestation weighing 1300 g, and the other patient was born at 40 weeks' gestation weighing 1320 g. The patients, aged 12 and 5.5 years, had severe short stature and extreme microcephaly with mild developmental delay. Both also had multiple brain aneurysms and moyamoya disease (see 252350). Further analyses suggested that this mutation was transmitted through an unknown common ancestor because both patients were identical for all polymorphic sites identified within the PCNT region.</Attribute>
